<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5240641>
    dc:description "FIGURE 15. Gastronyssus philippinensis Bochkov et OConnor, sp. nov., female (A–D). A, tibia and tarsus I in dorsal view; B, tibia and tarsus II in dorsal view; C, tarsus and posterior part of tibia III in dorsal view; D, tarsus and posterior part of tibia IV in dorsal view. Male (E–J). E, genu III in lateral view; F, aedeagus; G, anterior part of aedeagus; H, tibia and tarsus I in dorsal view; I, tibia and tarsus II in dorsal view; J, place of fusion of sternum with distal ends of apodemes II and posterior sclerites of coxal fields II. Scale bars: 100 µm (F,J), 50 µm (A–E, G–I)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/5240641/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

